A police inspector, Haruna Kawura, with the Imo State command has been found dead within the Shell camp police quarters in Owerri. Also, 45-year-old Osita Ezuruike has been discovered dead in his house, after he committed suicide in Umudafa, Awo Mbieri, in Mbaitoli local government area of Imo State. The Shell camp police estate is just about one kilometre away from the state headquarters of the police in Owerri. Sources told LEADERSHIP that the officer was discovered lying dead on the road inside the police quarters just opposite Alvana Primary School. Meanwhile, the police command has commenced investigation into the mystery surrounding Kawura’s death as the police medical team has evacuated his body from the staff quarters. The police public relations officer, Orlando Ikeokwu, who confirmed the development, added that the mystery would be solved in the coming days. According to him, Kawura had marks on his body, suggestive of a scuffle, though he maintained that investigations were ongoing. He dismissed claims of Covid 19 symptoms, saying the late officer was at his duty post on Monday, and even hung out with friends at the close of work. He said though the cause of the death is still unknown but everyone having contact with it observed precautionary measures especially in the face of  global COVID-19 pandemic. He assured that the command will soon come up with the exact cause of the death as investigation to unravel the root cause has commenced. On Ezuruike, Orlando said the victim did not drop any suicide note. According to him, the late Ezuruike had been experiencing a hard time fending for himself and family.  Ikeokwu said investigations had also commenced into the circumstances surrounding the death of Ezuruike.